Issues.Body:
**What version of Tailwind CSS are you using?**
4.1.11

**What build tool (or framework if it abstracts the build tool) are you using?**

 "postcss": "^8.5.4",
 "postcss-cli": "^11.0.1"

**What version of Node.js are you using?**

"node": "22.4.1"

**What browser are you using?**

N/A

**What operating system are you using?**

macOS

**Reproduction URL*

https://github.com/Intrepidd/tailwind-broken-classes-repro

**Describe your issue**

I encountered this issue when deploying my code.
My CSS got broken after I added the RubyTree gem to my code, I realized tailwindcss parsed my `vendor/ruby` directory that contained all the code of all the gems I'm using.

[This particular file](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/evolve75/RubyTree/f99daed0289274485a5f7e0786b773b4acbb5f08/TODO.org) seems to have broken my CSS by adding the following classes to my output CSS: 

```
  .\[file\:\.travis\.yml\]\[\.travis\.yml\] {
    file: .travis.yml][.travis.yml;
  }
  .\[file\:COPYING\.rdoc\]\[COPYING\.rdoc\] {
    file: COPYING.rdoc][COPYING.rdoc;
  }
  .\[file\:lib\/tree\/b\]\[BinaryTree\] {
    file: lib/tree/b][BinaryTree;
  }
```
